I would have thought you'd know by now that by providing the URL you
avoid the need to post the markup or the URL of the stylesheet, and by
providing either the URL or the CSS filespec (even alone) you obviate
the need to post the CSS.

<QUOTE PREVIOUSPOST="
&gt; How can I get the topmenulogin class to go to the top so it is next to
&gt; topmenu? I have tried placing the topmenulogin as a div class inside
&gt; of the tags for the topmenu div and using span class=topmenulogin
&gt; inside of the topmenu class div but the outcome is the same.
">

If by &quot;next to&quot; you mean &quot;on an approximate horizontal level with&quot; then
you can try swapping the .topmenu and .topmenulogin divs. I know it's
weird but it works in my FF.

You might also go ahead and remove the &lt;pre&gt;&lt;/pre&gt; tags from around your
form &lt;input&gt;s.

You can remove the &lt;p&gt; or &lt;div&gt; markup from .topmenu; you don't need
both. And you can also excise the .topmenuseparator class from markup
and CSS. Just give .topmenu the declarationsyour currently in your
.topmenuseparator, and provide &quot;red&quot; declarations for the selector
&quot;.topmenu a&quot;, since I presume you'll be adding &lt;a&gt; markup to Home,
About, etc.

Don't specify font sizes in px; use % (start with 100 of them on body).

--
John
